# Traceability Standards

## Required hierarchy (ADO)

Every User Story → parent Feature → parent Epic (when epics are used).

## Polarion ↔ ADO

| Relationship | When required |
|--------------|---------------|
| Requirement **implements** Story/Feature | Story delivers regulated or specified requirement |
| Requirement **verifies** TestCase | Validation against Polarion test cases |
| Feature ↔ Epic | Program-level traceability |

## Audit checklist

Before closing a Story tied to Polarion requirements:

1. Parent Feature exists and is linked
2. Polarion requirement link exists (`get_work_item_links` / ADO relations)
3. Acceptance criteria cover requirement intent (not full spec paste)
4. Review/approval status checked if item is under formal review (`list_reviewers`)

## Orphan detection

Use `traceability-auditor` agent or `polarion-requirements-steward` skill to find:

- Polarion requirements with no implementing ADO item
- ADO Stories with no parent Feature
- Stories referencing platform delivery without Platform Decision and Rationale

Do not create links in Polarion or ADO without explicit user confirmation unless they asked to "fix traceability."
